                "value": 0.011
              },
              "free_text": [
                "  1.1 +/- 0.1%",
                "Enriched 18O target in 18O2 gas, Si[18O]2 and Al2[18O]3",
                " composition of the gas targets. Chemical purity>99.9%",
                "Si[18O]2    18O Content 95 +-3%",
                "Al2[18O]3   18O Content 83 +-5%",
                "The gas cells made of stainless steel 2 cm diam. and",
                " 2.5 cm length.",
                "Gas pressure: 0.4 - 1.5 bar. 100 um Al windows were",
                " used.",
                "Si[18O]2 targets were made by sedimentation on Al from",
                " 5 mg of Si[18O]2 powder.",
                "Al2[18O]3 targets were prepared by electrochemical",
                " oxidation of Al",
                "The thickness of the Al2[18O]3 layer was measured by",
                " SIMS."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "EXTB",
                "STTA",
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Stacked-gas cells and stacked-foil technique as well",
                " as single target irradiation were used. Al2[18O]3",
                " target were irradiated one by one at low energies up",
                " to 7 MeV with about 100 nA for about 30 min.",
                "Beam current was measured by Faraday cup.",
                "Stacked gas targets were irradiated with 100 nA",
                " protons for 5 to 15 min.",
                "Beam current was monitored with copper foils.",
                "Stacks made of Al2[18O]3 and Si[18O]2 were irradiated",
                " for 15 min by 200 to 300 nA proton beam.",
                "Cu an Ti foils were used to degrade the beam energy",
                " and also served as monitor foils."
              ]
            }
          ],
